http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Drones-will-not-be-allowed/article14022574.ece

Professional drones fitted with cameras or quadcopters with cameras will not be allowed to film or photograph the International Fleet Review (IFR) proceedings on February 7, when the International City Parade, operations demonstration by Marcos (Marine Commandos) and Prime Minister Narendra Modi will address gathering at RK Beach in Visakhapatnam.To make security tighter, the 1.5 lakh people who have taken the passes will only be allowed to entry into the beach area . The pass holders will also have to carry some identity card.